Perfect bro üî• ‚Äî these errors are 100% Angular module/import related, not logic issues.
They happen when we use Angular structural directives (*ngIf, *ngFor, ngClass, ngForm)
without importing the right modules in your app setup.

Let‚Äôs fix all of them step-by-step and cleanly üëá

‚∏ª

‚ö†Ô∏è Errors You‚Äôre Seeing

Error	Root Cause
NgIf used but not imported	Missing CommonModule import
NgFor used but not imported	Missing CommonModule import
ngClass not a known property	Missing CommonModule import
No directive found with exportAs ngForm	Missing FormsModule or ReactiveFormsModule import
Expected 0 arguments but got 1	Usually from incorrect FormBuilder.group() or service method call


‚∏ª

‚úÖ FIX 1 ‚Äì Update app.module.ts

Please open src/app/app.module.ts (if it‚Äôs named differently like app.ts, adjust accordingly).
Replace the imports & declarations with this clean, complete version üëá

‚úÖ app.module.ts

import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { FormsModule, ReactiveFormsModule } from '@angular/forms';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { RouterModule } from '@angular/router';

import { AppComponent } from './app';
import { TravellComponent } from './travell/travell';
import { TravelDetailsComponent } from './travel-details/travel-details';
import { ApprovalsComponent } from './approvals/approvals';
import { WelcomeComponent } from './welcome/welcome';

import { TravelService } from './services/travel';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [
    AppComponent,
    TravellComponent,
    TravelDetailsComponent,
    ApprovalsComponent,
    WelcomeComponent
  ],
  imports: [
    BrowserModule,
    CommonModule,              // ‚úÖ Required for *ngIf, *ngFor, ngClass, etc.
    FormsModule,               // ‚úÖ Required for Template-driven forms
    ReactiveFormsModule,       // ‚úÖ Required for Reactive forms (FormBuilder)
    RouterModule.forRoot([
      { path: '', component: WelcomeComponent },
      { path: 'new-travel', component: TravellComponent },
      { path: 'travel-details', component: TravelDetailsComponent },
      { path: 'approvals', component: ApprovalsComponent }
    ])
  ],
  providers: [TravelService],
  bootstrap: [AppComponent]
})
export class AppModule {}

‚úÖ This imports everything you need:
	‚Ä¢	CommonModule ‚Üí for *ngIf, *ngFor, ngClass
	‚Ä¢	FormsModule ‚Üí for ngForm
	‚Ä¢	ReactiveFormsModule ‚Üí for FormBuilder
	‚Ä¢	RouterModule ‚Üí for navigation
	‚Ä¢	Registered all components properly

